    source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Osmium
    period: 1
    phase: Solid
    summary: "Osmium (from Greek osme (\u1F40\u03C3\u03BC\u03AE) meaning \"smell\")
      is a chemical element with symbol Os and atomic number 76. It is a hard, brittle,
      bluish-white transition metal in the platinum group that is found as a trace
      element in alloys, mostly in platinum ores. Osmium is the densest naturally
      occurring element, with a density of 7004225900000000000\u266022.59 g/cm3."
    boil: 5285
