    summary: Selenium is a chemical element with symbol Se and atomic number 34.
      It is a nonmetal with properties that are intermediate between those of its
      periodic table column-adjacent chalcogen elements sulfur and tellurium. It
      rarely occurs in its elemental state in nature, or as pure ore compounds.
    boil: 958
