    summary: 'Zinc, in commerce also spelter, is a chemical element with symbol Zn
      and atomic number 30. It is the first element of group 12 of the periodic table.
      In some respects zinc is chemically similar to magnesium: its ion is of similar
      size and its only common oxidation state is +2.'
