    summary: Rutherfordium is a chemical element with symbol Rf and atomic number
      104, named in honor of physicist Ernest Rutherford. It is a synthetic element
      (an element that can be created in a laboratory but is not found in nature)
      and radioactive; the most stable known isotope, 267Rf, has a half-life of approximately
      1.3 hours. In the periodic table of the elements, it is a d - block element
      and the second of the fourth - row transition elements.
    boil: 5800
