    period: 1
    phase: Solid
    summary: 'Niobium, formerly columbium, is a chemical element with symbol Nb (formerly
      Cb) and atomic number 41. It is a soft, grey, ductile transition metal, which
      is often found in the pyrochlore mineral, the main commercial source for niobium,
      and columbite. The name comes from Greek mythology: Niobe, daughter of Tantalus
      since it is so similar to tantalum.'
    boil: 5017
