      in the periodic table that has the temporary symbol Uup and has the atomic
      number 115. It is an extremely radioactive element; its most stable known isotope,
      ununpentium-289, has a half-life of only 220 milliseconds. It is also known
      as eka-bismuth or simply element 115.
