    summary: Scandium is a chemical element with symbol Sc and atomic number 21.
      A silvery-white metallic d-block element, it has historically been sometimes
      classified as a rare earth element, together with yttrium and the lanthanoids.
      It was discovered in 1879 by spectral analysis of the minerals euxenite and
      gadolinite from Scandinavia.
