      It is an extremely radioactive synthetic element (an element that can be created
      in a laboratory but is not found in nature); the most stable known isotope,
      roentgenium-282, has a half-life of 2.1 minutes. Roentgenium was first created
      in 1994 by the GSI Helmholtz Centre for Heavy Ion Research near Darmstadt,
      Germany.
