    summary: 'Fluorine is a chemical element with symbol F and atomic number 9. It
      is the lightest halogen and exists as a highly toxic pale yellow diatomic gas
      at standard conditions. As the most electronegative element, it is extremely
      reactive: almost all other elements, including some noble gases, form compounds
      with fluorine.'
    boil: 85
