    summary: Palladium is a chemical element with symbol Pd and atomic number 46.
      It is a rare and lustrous silvery-white metal discovered in 1803 by William
      Hyde Wollaston. He named it after the asteroid Pallas, which was itself named
      after the epithet of the Greek goddess Athena, acquired by her when she slew
      Pallas.
