    summary: Yttrium is a chemical element with symbol Y and atomic number 39. It
      is a silvery-metallic transition metal chemically similar to the lanthanides
      and it has often been classified as a "rare earth element". Yttrium is almost
      always found combined with the lanthanides in rare earth minerals and is never
      found in nature as a free element.
    boil: 3203
