    summary: Ytterbium is a chemical element with symbol Yb and atomic number 70.
      It is the fourteenth and penultimate element in the lanthanide series, which
      is the basis of the relative stability of its +2 oxidation state. However,
      like the other lanthanides, its most common oxidation state is +3, seen in
      its oxide, halides and other compounds.
    boil: 1469
