    summary: Americium is a radioactive transuranic chemical element with symbol
      Am and atomic number 95. This member of the actinide series is located in the
      periodic table under the lanthanide element europium, and thus by analogy was
      named after the Americas. Americium was first produced in 1944 by the group
      of Glenn T.Seaborg from Berkeley, California, at the metallurgical laboratory
      of University of Chicago.
