      number 116. It is an extremely radioactive element that has only been created
      in the laboratory and has not been observed in nature. The element is named
      after the Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory in the United States, which
      collaborated with the Joint Institute for Nuclear Research in Dubna, Russia
      to discover livermorium in 2000.
