    summary: Nitrogen is a chemical element with symbol N and atomic number 7. It
      is the lightest pnictogen and at room temperature, it is a transparent, odorless
      diatomic gas. Nitrogen is a common element in the universe, estimated at about
      seventh in total abundance in the Milky Way and the Solar System.
    boil: 77
